  "body": "I think we could do with a shadow-before-use warning, if a variable goes unused before it is shadowed, eg.:\n\n```\nlet a = ...\nlet a = ... // proposed warning (I meant b)\nf(a);\nf(b); // error; did you mean a?\n```\n\nI don't have strong feelings about this but it does find the mistake on the line where it occurred, which would be especially nice for editors that mark lines with warnings.\n",
